# Frontend Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values:

```bash
## Chain & Contract Configuration

# Contract Address (deploy first, then set this)
VITE_CONTRACT_ADDRESS=0x...
DATABASE_URL=""

# Chain configuration (defaults to Polygon mainnet)
VITE_CHAIN_ID=137
VITE_RPC_URL=https://polygon-rpc.com
VITE_CHAIN_NAME=Polygon
VITE_BLOCK_EXPLORER_URL=https://polygonscan.com/

## Backend API
# Backend API URL (default: http://localhost:3001/api)
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001/api

## IPFS
# Optional: IPFS Gateway URL (for displaying IPFS content)
VITE_IPFS_GATEWAY=https://ipfs.io/ipfs/
```

## Getting Started

1. Deploy the contract to Polygon (mainnet or testnet as desired)
2. Copy the deployed contract address
3. Create `.env` file in `frontend/` directory
4. Set `VITE_CONTRACT_ADDRESS` to your deployed contract address
5. Set `VITE_CHAIN_ID` and `VITE_RPC_URL` if not using Polygon mainnet
6. Set `VITE_API_URL` to your backend API URL (if different from default)
7. Run `npm run dev` or `pnpm dev`

